com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Class NullFieldGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.NullOrderedCollection<Field>
      • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.NullFieldGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FieldGroup, Nullable, OrderedCollection<Field>, OrderedCollectionOfFields, OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed<Field>

    public final class NullFieldGroup
extends NullOrderedCollection<Field>
implements FieldGroup
    A distinguished FieldGroup variant for indicating a field group with no contents.

    This field group:

    • Is a singleton (see INSTANCE) and may not be cloned
    • Is immutable
    • Contains no fields
    • Is equal only with itself

      • visitDepthFirst

        public void visitDepthFirst(BytesFieldVisitor visitor)
        Description copied from interface: FieldGroup
        Have all this field groups nested fields visited by the specified visitor.

        Implementations must try to ensure that no additional field objects are consumed and attempt to pass ByteArrayView values to the visitor where possible.

        Where Field object are already consumed then they must take precedence over the underlying ByteArrayView value and be passed to the visitor.

        Specified by:

        public boolean remove(int key)
        Description copied from interface: OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed
